text: When I was little, I loved magic. The key to magic is not knowing how a trick is done because once you know, then it is not fun anymore. I think Penn and Teller have the best act because they do a magic trick, show you how it was done and then do the same trick with a twist which violates every logic that was presented in their original explanation of the trick to keep it fun. There is an old movie called Houdini starring Tony Curtis that was fun. It captured the story behind Houdini and shows how some of his tricks were performed. So with the exception of Houdini (the movie), my personal opinion is that movies about magic should not be made. In a movie with editing and special effects, anything can be done. There is no "magic" and everyone knows it.
